Package: VibeCluster
Type: Package
Title: Mood-Based Music Clustering and Recommendation via K-Means and
        PCA
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-03-13
Authors@R: person("Student", "Author", email = "author@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: MusicMoodMapper clusters songs into mood groups using k-means
    clustering on audio features such as energy, valence, danceability, tempo,
    acousticness, and loudness. Principal Component Analysis (PCA) is used to
    visualise the mood landscape in 2-D, and a k-Nearest Neighbours (kNN)
    classifier lets users input their own feature vector to receive personalised
    song recommendations. The package ships with a built-in dataset of 400
    labelled tracks and supports user-supplied CSV files. Mood labels (Happy,
    Melancholic, Energetic, Calm, Angry, Romantic) are inferred automatically
    from cluster centroids and can be overridden. The elbow method and silhouette
    analysis assist with choosing k.
